org.pircbotx.hooks.events

Class OwnerEvent<T extends PircBotX>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pircbotx.hooks.Event<T>
      • org.pircbotx.hooks.events.OwnerEvent<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericEvent<T>, GenericUserModeEvent<T>

    public class OwnerEvent<T extends PircBotX>
extends Event<T>
implements GenericUserModeEvent<T>
    Called when a user (possibly us) gets owner status granted in a channel. Note that this isn't supported on all servers or may be used for something else

    This is a type of mode change and therefor is also dispatched in a ModeEvent

    Author:
    Leon Blakey
